5:
This is the Adventurers' Guild. A lot of
the students from the academy
come here too, you know?
7:
Some of them do adventuring
secretly on the side for some extra
cash, to get rare materials, or even
to make a request of their own...
9:
Some of the Shibuyans with powers
are becoming adventurers, too.
Shota is one of them.
16:
Hey, don't usually see you guys here.
You taking on a request?
19: Hehe. I'm on a date with Hibiki today.
27:
I still don't know anything about
Shibuya, or Palpebra... or anything at
all, really...
29: So I decided I wanted to learn more.
31:
That's when Luciada said she'd show
me around...
36:
Hey, that's perfect! The two of us'll
tag along—
41:
We've already taken on a request,
so we can't hang out today. Have
fun, you two!
45:
This is the busiest market district in
Palpebra.
47:
Here, you can find anything from all
kinds of food, household goods, and
even local specialties.
50:
That's right! I had this one drink for
the first time the other day...
Bubble-something?
56:
Hate to be the one to break it to you,
but that bubble-something stall's
been gone for a while now.
58:
I can't really offer anything similar to
that, but why don't you take a look
at my wares? You're from Voluntas
Academy, right?
61:
Hmm... Is this a potion catalyst? It
appears to be of high quality. What
other sorts of things are you sel—
65:
Wait! What am I doing? Standing
around shopping like it's a normal
day!
73:
It's NOT! Today's the day I'm
supposed to be showing you around!
76:
Is there anywhere you'd like to visit,
Hibiki?
79:
Um... Maybe a music store, or
something?
83:
Hehe! That sounds just right for you,
Hibiki! Don't worry, I did my research
ahead of time!
96:
I think we... took a wrong turn
somewhere.
113:
Don't worry. I can at least get us
back to where we started.
119:
I'm sorry, Hibiki... I still haven't walked
around Palpebra that much myself,
actually...
123:
Well... I kind of had that impression
from the start.
127:
It's just... I still only know you for
"Binary Planet"...
130:
So I wanted to know more about
you. And not just your music, but
about who you are as a person,
Hibiki.
138:
But I guess I kind of jumped the gun.
I'm sorry for all the trouble I've
caused you.
146:
Why are you researching golems,
Luciada?
151:
Hm? Oh, well... It's just cool for one
thing... And it's fun to put together
command procedures, and things
like that...
153:
But I think more than anything, I do it
because I see their potential.
155:
If we can develop golems far
enough, we could let them handle a
number of different jobs and make
things easier for everyone.
157:
That would probably create its own
share of problems... But overall, I
think everyone's lives will be
enriched.
160:
That's why I decided to research
golems.
164:
...I'm honestly surprised you gave
me an in-depth answer like that.
167: What do you mean by that?
171:
But I think this is the right way to go
about everything.
174:
You don't have to keep pulling me
along. We can take our time in
getting to know each other better.
178:
That's how I'd like us to spend our
time together, Luciada.
185:
Hehe! I think I've learned something
new and wonderful about you, Hibiki.
188:
And I think I've become pretty
familiar with a disappointing side of
you too, Luciada.
191:
Heh-heh. Would you care to
elaborate on that?
